race.comment: PINOT NERO (4) backed up a strong second here two runs back with a narrow win over this trip at Scone eight days ago. Finds another suitable race and can go back-to-back. IT IS TO BE (2) was narrowly beaten at Canberra over 2000m last start and drops in grade. Won over this track and trip the run prior and looks set to feature again. FINAL IMPACT (3) hasn't broken through for a while but keeps knocking. Was solid behind PINOT NERO last time and now gets weight relief over the winner. SHADOW SHOT (1) was close at Mudgee and is peaking fourth-up. One of the key hopes. CAVORTING (5) hasn't fired lately but earlier form reads well. Each-way chance.
